1. Create a two-dimensional array. Fill in with random numbers. Sort each line by growth.
2. Create a two-dimensional array. Fill in with random numbers. Find the arithmetic mean of the matrix diagonals
3. Create a two-dimensional array. Fill in with random numbers. Find the number that is repeated most times.
4. Given an array of size N. 
Find two adjacent elements whose sum is maximal, and deduce these elements in the order of increasing their indexes.
5. Given an array of N. Find the number of its last local maximum 
(the local maximum is an element that is larger than any of its neighbors).
6. Fulfill the tasks discussed in pairs.
